# Deploy after changes

This repo is connected to Vercel via the GitHub integration: every push to `main` triggers an automatic production deploy. Do **not** run `vercel deploy` manually — it duplicates the deploy and is slower.

After completing substantive code edits (features, fixes, refactors that affect runtime):

1. Run `npm run build` and fix any failures before pushing.
2. `git add -A` → commit with a descriptive message → `git push origin main`.
3. Trust the GitHub → Vercel hook to publish; no `npx vercel deploy` call.

Skip the push only when the user explicitly says not to ship or when changes are documentation-only with no effect on the app.
